  "texts": [
    "To complement the analysis of orientation, we further examined the connectivity of the hydrogen bond network through geodesic distance analysis in the same interfacial region.",
    "The geodesic distance here is defined as the average number of hydrogen bonds forming the shortest path between two water molecules within the largest connected hydrogenbond cluster, and thus it is a dimensionless measure of hydrogen-bond connectivity.",
    "The cluster refers to a group of water molecules connected through at least one hydrogen bond, forming a single continuous network.",
    "Surprisingly, the average geodesic length was found to be larger for the hydrophilic surface (24.15) compared to the hydrophobic surface (23.71).",
    "This counterintuitive result can be attributed to the interaction between water molecules and the surface."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}